Since its formation in 2016, the food pantry has made 9,970 disbursements.

The School of General Studies has received approximately 21 percent of these disbursements. It is the leading receiver of disbursements with a total of 2,088 despite making up only 6.5 percent of the total student popluation as of 2021. This is followed by the Graduate School of Engineering and Applied Science (11 percent of the student body population) with 1,707 disbursements and the Graduate School of Arts and Sciences (8 percent of the student body population) with 1,042.
